[![Press Freedom Day events](https://globalvoicesonline.org/wp-
content/uploads/2014/04/Press-Freedom-
Day.png)](https://worldpressfreedomday2014.crowdmap.com/)

Screen shot of UNESCO's crowd map of Press Freedom Day events

May 3 is World Press Freedom Day and UNESCO is marking the occasion with an
event in Paris, France that is [free and open to the
public](http://www.unesco-ci.org/cmscore/civicrm/event/info?reset=1&id=25).

There are lots of resources [on their
site](http://www.unesco.org/new/en/unesco/events/prizes-and-
celebrations/celebrations/international-days/world-press-freedom-
day/homepage/) for anyone who wishes to learn more about press freedom or host
an event.

Using an online crowdmapping tool UNESCO [is logging World Press Freedom Day
events](https://worldpressfreedomday2014.crowdmap.com/) around the world and
invite you to [submit your
own](https://worldpressfreedomday2014.crowdmap.com/reports/submit).

[UNESCO](http://www.unesco.org/) is the United Nations Educational, Scientific
and Cultural Organization.

